# Author User Docs — TEACH (Project Overlay)

The full skill — the two altitudes, the record-is-source genre boundary, the Diátaxis four quadrants, and the validated-behavior-only rule — is in the `praxis` plugin's `author-user-docs` skill. Read it first.

## Project-specific paths

- Capability guides: `{{paths.guides}}/<capability>/` (concepts + how-tos)
- Journey tutorials: `{{paths.guides}}/tutorials/` (cross-capability walkthroughs)
- Source of truth: the capability record at `{{paths.architecture}}/<capability>/`
- User voice / journeys: the wave `product-design.md` under `{{paths.waves}}/`

## Project-specific gates

- Owned by the product designer (`.github/agents/{{personas.aliases.product-designer}}.agent.md`); the principal engineer reviews technical accuracy.
- Author only after the behavior has shipped and the capability record reflects it — never teach a hypothesis.
- Fires from `close-sprint` only when user-observable behavior changed; a pure refactor skips TEACH.
- Each guide carries `source:` and `last-validated:` front-matter and links back from the capability record.
